by various disciplines. Choices of research methodology here depend on research questions and theoretical framework conditions. In keeping with the diversity of issues and approaches, research on second language acquisition can employ a broad spectrum of methodological procedures. This volume addresses highly diverse empirical methods, the advantages and limitations of which are described by the authors with reference to concrete research projects. In this way the volume aims to provide insights into research on second language acquisitions in a multilingual society and to offer suggestions for further research projects.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aGerman languagexStudy and teaching (Elementary)xForeign speakers. 0aLanguage and languagesxStudy and teaching. 0aSecond language acquisition -- Research. 0aSecond language acquisitionxResearch. 0aSecond language acquisition. 4aSprachdidaktik. 4aZweitspracherwerb. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aLanguage Teaching.  aSecond Language Acquisition.1 aAhrenholz, Bernt, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAhrenholz, Bernt, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBecker, Angelika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrede, Julia Ricart, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarroll, Mary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDarsow, Annkathrin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDimroth, Christine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDittmar, Norbert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEllert, Miriam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFelbrich, Anja,